                <div id="versionCompareContent" class="WPC-editableContent">
                  <font size="2"><b><font color="DarkRed">Bahamar Quests</font></b><br />
                  tnx to Rosemary (iah forums and Gilliam)<br />
                  <br />
                  These quests continue on from the <a href="/page/Pioneering+Quests" target="_self" title="Pioneering Questline">Pioneering Questline</a><br />
                  <br />
                  <b>Quest: Bahamar Marshland</b><br />
                  <i>NPC+ Location: Igorne, Bahamar Base Camp<br />
                  Reward: 3x Exp Card, 3x Polish: Veteran and 3x Health Regen Potion<br /></i> After giving the Letter of recommendation to the Igorne, he will ask you to collect 6 Seal of the Pioneer Lv 9 from the Bahamas Swamp. [For extra info, these are also ingredients needed for necklace recipes]. You need to kill 150 Swamp Spider Crab per seal so 900 spiders in total. Some people will also sell these in the Market Manager.<br />
                  After getting all 6 Seals of the Pioneer Lv 9 return and talk to Igorne again.<br /></font><br />
                  <font size="2"><br />
                  <b>Quest: Pioneering of the Bahamar Swamp</b><br />
                  <i>NPC+ Location: Igorne, Bahamar Base Camp<br />
                  Reward: 3x Exp Card, ?x Hermes Potion, ?x Health Regen Potion and 3x Polish: Veteran<br /></i> Igorne&rsquo;s secretary, Sharon will come and report about a troubling monster lurking in the Bahamar Swamp. Igorne then gives you the task to kill the Swamp Angler: a rare boss that can be found throughout the Bahamar region. It is somewhat difficult to take it on alone and since it&rsquo;s a quest item, it&rsquo;s recommended to do it in squads.<br />
                  After killing it, return and talk to Igorne to receive your reward.<br />
                  <br /></font> <font size="2"><img align="bottom" alt="Pioneering Quests - Wiki of the new world" height="757" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/1/RhMDm0Enc8zM92kqYcBPig121969/GW1011H757" title="Pioneering Quests - Wiki of the new world" width="1011" /></font><br />
                  <font size="2"><br />
                  <br />
                  <b>Quest: Unknown Enemy</b><br /></font> <font size="2"><i>NPC+ Location: Igorne, Bahamar Base Camp</i></font><br />
                  <font size="2"><i>Reward:</i></font><br />
                  <font size="2">After completing the Swamp Angler quest, leave the map and return to trigger this quest.</font><br />
                  <font size="2">Igorne and Sharon now task you to look for the land of the witches. They think that the Bahamar Swamp of Eternity is a possible place where the witches are hiding, so they ask you to go investigate. Head to the Witch&#39;s House at G6 in Bahamar Swamp of Eternity.<br />
                  Once you step inside the Witch&rsquo;s House you will be sent to an instance so be prepared before you enter. The witches will summon 3 Bahamar enemies; L110 Taurus, L110 Locke and a L110 Pink wing frog and you need to eliminate all of them.<br />
                  After some dialogue, return back to Igorne to receive your reward.<br />
                  <br />
                  <br />
                  <b>Quest: Land of Witch</b><br />
                  <i>NPC+ Location: Igorne, Bahamar Base Camp<br />
                  Reward: 3x Exp Card (100k), 20x Mithridart, 5x Teleport Scroll and 3x Polish:Veteran.<br /></i> Returning to the Witch&rsquo;s house, you will find that it&rsquo;s being sealed by the witch to stop trespassers (i.e. you). It&rsquo;s then suggested that in order to remove the seal, you need to go to various monuments scattered across Bahamar, and use Otites to absorb the magic that is binding the seal. The Otites are provided as a quest item by Igorne.<br />
                  <br />
                  Bahamar Marshlands:<br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/1/izYDTntkeLQf_6jPaiX3CQ60875" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  Bahamar Swamp of Eternity:<br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/1/-K_SefgwXY1zD7XI2x_qRA62601" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  Bahamar Swamp of Darkness:<br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/1/YxBI3jm1kPeIqg5v6jfr8g58599" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  Bahamar Swamp of Peril:<br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/1/T0gNDv7YFXwXUlvSHUPSVg61191" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  Just go up the monument with the Otites in hand and the magic will be sealed. After visiting all 8 monuments, return to Igorne and receive your reward. The next quest will immediately start.<br />
                  <br />
                  <br />
                  <b>Quest: Witch Suppression</b><br />
                  <i>NPC+ Location: Igorne, Bahamar Base Camp<br />
                  Reward: 3x Exp Card (100k), 3x Defensive, Fillers 3x Polish: Veteran and 1x Gift Box (quest item).<br /></i> Igorne will send you to the Witch&#39;s House to fight them. When you enter the warp, you&#39;ll be sent to an instance and fight several Bahamar monsters. Afterwards, talk to Igorne. When he&#39;s done you&#39;ll be sent to an instance involving a conversation between Sharon, Igorne and the two witches. After they stop talking you&#39;ll fight Sharon, who&#39;s pretty easy. When she&#39;s dead, more talking.<br />
                  <br />
                  <img align="bottom" alt="Sharon Part 1" height="194" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/1/gg2TVjWUNsXIRm_cxhjIGg93487/GW340H194" title="Sharon Part 1" width="340" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <br />
                  <b>Quest: Sierra&#39;s House</b><br />
                  <i>NPC+ Location: Ignorne, Bahamar Base Camp<br />
                  Reward: 1x Invisible Potion, 3x Exp Card (100k) and 3x Polish: Veteran.<br /></i> Continuing from Witch Suppression go to the Witch&#39;s House and talk to Leonora. She&#39;ll warp you to Sierra&#39;s house. Talk to her to give her the Gift Box. She&#39;ll reward you with an Invisible Potion.<br />
                  Talk to Igorne again to receive your reward.<br />
                  <br />
                  <br />
                  <b>Quest: Status of Lenora</b><br />
                  <i>NPC+ Location: Igorne, Bahamar Base Camp<br />
                  Reward: 3x Hermes Potion, 3x Exp Card (100k) and 6x Polish: Veteran.<br /></i> Talk to Igorne and he will ask you to visit the Witch&rsquo;s House to see how they are doing.<br />
                  Leonora tells you that Sierra is down with a fever, and she will ask for your help to create a remedy.<br />
                  &ldquo;Mysterious Medicine&rdquo; quest will start (see below quest).<br />
                  Once you have collected completed the medicine quest, give the medicine to Sierra. Return to Igorne and the quest will be complete.<br />
                  <br />
                  <br />
                  <b>Quest: Mysterious Medicine</b><br />
                  <i>NPC+ Location: Leonora, Witch&#39;s House<br />
                  Reward: Mysterious medicine of Leonora, 3x Exp Cards (100k) and 3x Polish: Veteran.<br /></i> The medicine requires: Mysterious water, Pure Etreniaum x100, Aidanium x100 and Quartz x 100.<br />
                  The Mysterious Water is dropped by Elite Wasp that appears in Bahamar Swamp of Eternity.<br />
                  Once you gather all the materials, talk to Leonora and she will give you the Mysterious medicine of Leonora and warp you to Sierra&#39;s House<br />
                  <br />
                  <br />
                  <b>Quest: Visit</b><br />
                  <i>NPC+ Location: Igorne, Bahamar Base Camp<br />
                  Reward: Blade of the Emperor recipe, 3x Exp Card (100k), 6x Polish: Veteran and 3x Enchant Boosters.<br /></i> Knowing that Sierra is sick, Igorne goes to visit her and wants you to come along. Go to the Witch&#39;s House and talk to Leonora. You will discovered that Sierra has been kidnapped. You will be warped immediately to an instance called &ldquo;Kidnapped Sierra&rdquo;. After some dialogue with Fritz joining your side of the battle you will have to fight against Sharon and three Bahamar monsters. Afterwards there&#39;ll be some more dialogue and then talk to Fritz to end the instance.<br />
                  <br />
                  <img align="bottom" alt="Sharon Part 2" height="193" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/1/Z_Rgap34Wm4eW1tH8xqxlQ97095/GW340H193" title="Sharon Part 2" width="340" /><br />
                  <br />
                  After defeating her, you will return to the Witch&rsquo;s home and Leonora will give you a Chess Series recipe - Blade of the Emperor . The Chess Series recipes can then be purchased from here on for 10m each. Also Leonora can warp you to Sierra&#39;s House.<br />
                  Return to Igorne to complete the quest.<br />
                  <br />
                  <br />
                  <b>Quest: Ten Nobles of Vespanola</b><br />
                  <i>NPC+ Location: Igorne, Bahamar Base Camp<br />
                  Reward: Witch&#39;s Hat, 3x Polish: Veteran and a Triumph Filler.<br /></i> After talking Igorne, you will receive Grenmah&rsquo;s Letter. Feeling suspicious and troubled with the ways of Vespanola, Igorne decides to return to Auch for answers. Before returning to Auch, Igorne wants to bid farewell to Sierra. After talking to Leonora you&#39;ll be warped to an instance where Grenmah and Fritz will be talking. After, talk to Leonora again and warp to Sierra&#39;s House. Talk to Sierra and she will reward you will the Witch&#39;s Hat as a farewell gift.<br />
                  Return to Auch and talk to Elenore for your reward.<br />
                  <br />
                  <br />
                  <br />
                  <br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Garcia Questline</span><br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">tnx to Astaros</span></font><br />
                  <font size="2"><span class="diffRemove">Please ensure that you have finished the following quests otherwise you cannot activate his quest:</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">- The Pioneering quest (finishing the Bahamas Swamp section)</span><br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">- The entire Katovic Snowfield Quest series (giving you access to the Ice Wizard tower and finishing the original soup quest)</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/IcjbS_8W2N2_J3jlAiF3Kw240333" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Elenore&rsquo;s request</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/AGALcW_5NiN6xvnXeFd1jg248484" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Joaquin Expedition</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Continuing on, Elenore the Auch Pioneering Officer will ask you to catch Garcia, but she will send you to do an instanced mission called the Joaquin Expedition.</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/PfAzk_qqSBzgG77uXV_Pyw237659" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Simon&rsquo;s proposal - accept or decline</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Once you&rsquo;re done, head on and talk to Simon Ayende first. He will offer you two options, which would alter the storyline a little but no matter which option you chose you will still get Garcia&rsquo;s card for both routes.</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/alUmDy4lk-c16npWhXpUqg277585" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Location - Ferrucio Wall (F2)</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/r-jR3UJ40MYVtq5sDwWroA198633" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Meeting Selva Notre</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">After receiving either of the two missions, head to Ferrucio Wall, and there you will meet Selva. After some dialogue, go to the Frozen Plain and talk to Invernio to continue investigation of Feruccio&rsquo;s legacy. You will bump into Selva and Garcia again.</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/A0tCxutkhQxag-TWSha_dA254142" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Invernio&rsquo;s location</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Touching Reym&rsquo;s heart would allow you to know what exactly is Ferrucio&rsquo;s legacy, but before that, you need 50 gold bars, 50 ice crystals and 10 black magic stones.</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/RK-GAOwZQqmsFdIgRUbMqg222638" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Ice crystals and gold bars can be farmed throughout the Katovic map whereas black magic stones are dropped off mobs in the Ice Wizard Tower.</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/FbQHiDBincM8C3EniIR5TA200129" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">6 v 1, fair battle? xD</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">After solving the mystery of Reym&rsquo;s heart, Montoro will appear and steal the Ice Queen&rsquo;s seal. Selva, Garcia and Invernio will join your family in battle so you can attack from the corners. Here&rsquo;s Montoro&rsquo;s stats just in case:</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/oTekeVQl289wMJ9KpDLpIA129743" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Montoro&rsquo;s stats</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">At this point, you will receive this awesome item that adds 3AR and DR called Necklace of Sage. (Name may change due to different versions)</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/1cF6i5GdfAnmjyfdBM1eBA157657" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">The pendent will only remain in your inventory for three days and only one character may equip it</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">The next mission is to enter Ice Wizard Tower itself and defeat Novia. (Need to finish all katovic quests at this point to enter.)</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/dZn1tAv0oYt_tpzLvkmp5Q146134" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Once you entered the Ice Wizard Tower, move forward a few steps and a window will trigger asking you if you want to advance to the mission. Selecting yes will warp you to the instanced mission.</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/iNW5Gq76X0lSOHzUXtbSvA241326" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Once you&rsquo;re warped to the mission the battle will start against Novia. This will be no easy battle as you will not only face off Novia, but with her &ldquo;summons&rdquo; and Montoro. Selva and Garcia will aid you in the battle.</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/DkSjTshYcWxSvHcf-pHSsA377009" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Note</span><span class="diffRemove">: It is extra important you stand at the following spot as indicated if you even want an easy battle. It will give your family a buff of</span> <span class="diffRemove">AR/DR + 5</span> <span class="diffRemove">(It used to be 10 but the buff got nerfed as of ver 2.4) .You maybe fighting a quest version of Novia but nevertheless she&rsquo;s still a tough cookie.</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/YUU4I3mkPJxcsWV1Cvf7Ig333990" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">lvl 130 = Novia, lvl 110 = Montoro, lvl 120 = Novia&rsquo;s summons</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">You need to take down Montoro and her summons, and bring down Novia&rsquo;s HP to 50% before the quest is complete.</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">*Vital battle tip - Bring Elementalists or rNPCs with the lightning evocation stance; excluding Montoro, the others are very weak to lightning but remember to cover them while they spam away their skills</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">But after the battle, Garcia has been turned into the undead and you need to save him.</span><br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">So talk to Invernio again, and he will tell you that you need 10 soup and 10 gold bars to create a remedy to save Garcia. 1 soup requires 50 Wolf&rsquo;s meat, 20 Golden apples, 50 cabbages and 50 beets.</span><br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">[So you know what that means. 10 soup requires 500 Wolf&rsquo;s meat, 200 Golden apples, 500 cabbages and 500 beets.]</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Note:</span> <span class="diffRemove">If you have not done the soup quest in the Katovic Snowfield quest section, you will not be able to proceed to this part.</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">After saving Garcia, depending on what you chose when Simon offered you two choices, Garcia will either join you immediately or he will enter into a battle against you. But either way, you will get Garcia&rsquo;s card.</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Scenario 1</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/nDQg2jQv-3n4ZfeuFxCN4A203358" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">If you chose Simon&rsquo;s second option, which is to report to him after you have found/caught Garcia, you can get Garcia&rsquo;s card as your reward by talking to him back at Auch.</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Scenario 2</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">If you chose Simon&rsquo;s first option, which is to hand him over to the Office of Pioneering Support , you will be engaged into a battle with him.</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/Xze6GrhAbfxXCD7y6b0cpw91488" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">Garcia&rsquo;s stats</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">After you win/lose, Garcia will run off and you will need to find him. If you want to know his location, speak with Tiburon (ugh) and he will only tell you Garcia&rsquo;s location if you pay him 1,000,000 Vis.</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/3/amGuMPbG-J1VmLTryOEk6w391551" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" /><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">To those who have done Lorch&rsquo;s quest before, you should know better than to choose the 200,000 Vis offer.</span><br />
                  <br />
                  <span class="diffRemove">After you found his location, return to converse with Simon Ayende to receive Garcia&rsquo;s card AND a lvl 100 enchantment chip.</span><br /></font>
                </div><br class="clear" />
                <br class="clear" />
              </div>
